company_name: ISRO - Indian Institute of Remote Sensing (IIRS)
description: IIRS has collaborations with many reputed international organizations for capacity building, research and faculty exchange. The organizations with which IIRS has/had significant collaborations are: ITC, IHE (International Institute for Infrastructural, Hydraulic and Environmental Engineering) and Wageningen University in The Netherlands; ITTO (International Timber Research Organisation); UNESCO (United Nations Education & Scientific Cooperation Organisation); WMO (World Meteorological Organisation); ADPC (Asian Disaster Preparedness Centre); and NGI (Norwegian Geological Institute). Special mention may be made of its collaboration with ITC, The Netherlands, which spans over four decades, 1966 to date. The focus of the present phase of collaboration is to conduct Joint Education Programmes (JEP). Under the  JEP, two Masters Degree (M.Sc.) and two joint-logo Postgraduate Diploma programmes are conducted at IIRS in two specialisations – Geoinformatics and Natural Hazards & Disaster Risk Management.

company_name: ISRO - Indian Institute of Remote Sensing (IIRS)
description: Profile of Scientist and Non-Technical Staff Research Project Monitoring Department supports the mandated objective of IIRS by taking care of the sponsored research (RESPOND) activities of IIRS, ISRO. Sponsored Research activities at IIRS are carried out under various umbrellas including, RESPOND, Space Technology Cells (STC), Regional Academic Centres for Space (RAC-S), Space Technology Incubation Centres (S-TIC), YUKTI Sanchita, Atal Tinkering Labs. The main objective of the sponsored research programme of ISRO at IIRS is to establish strong linkages with premier academic institutions in the country to carry out research and developmental projects which are of relevance to IIRS, ISRO & and derive useful outputs of such R&D to support IIRS, ISRO programmes. Please refer to https://www.isro.gov.in/SponsoredResearch.html for more details on ISRO-Sponsored Research programmes

company_name: ISRO - Indian Institute of Remote Sensing (IIRS)
description: The training and capacity building programmes of the Institute are designed to meet the requirements of various target/user groups, i.e., for professionals at working, middle and supervisory levels, fresh graduates, researchers, academia and decision makers. The duration of courses ranges from one-week to two-years. The programmes are meticulously designed by the domain experts, and are then approved by the Board of Studies (BoS) and Academic Council (AC) consisting of eminent subject experts. A team of sixty-four dedicated scientists at IIRS contribute in delivering the course contents. Guest faculties from reputed organizations/institutes in the country and abroad are regularly invited to share their knowledge and experience with the course participants.
